  "prompt": "What referral bonus amounts do tech companies pay in LA?",
  "response": "Referral bonuses can vary widely among tech companies in Los Angeles depending on the company size, the level of the position being referred, and the specific policies of each company. While I don't have access to real-time, company-specific data, I can give you a general idea based on typical industry standards:\n\n1. **Large tech companies** (like Google, Amazon, Apple):\n   - Referral bonuses can range from $1,000 to $10,000 or more.\n\n2. **Mid-sized tech companies**:\n   - Bonuses usually fall in the $2,000 to $5,000 range.\n\n3. **Startups and smaller companies**:\n   - Referral bonuses can range from $500 to $3,000, depending on their budget and urgency for the position.\n\nAdditionally, some companies might offer non-monetary incentives such as extra vacation days, gift cards, or other perks.\n\nFor specific numbers, it's best to check directly with the company or network with employees of those companies in LA.",
